This announcement has been over a year in the making, and we are so, so grateful to our community for your support during this time of transition. Our founders, David and James, are taking a step back from day-to-day leadership, but the #Hidiocy is still strong! We are endlessly excited for the future of Hamlet Isn't Dead. Go to HamletIsntDead.com for the full memo and check out the link in our bio for details on our tenth birthday party! 
Love and Gratitude, 
Team HIDiot

Missing our #HIDiocy? Well don't you worry cuz we are teaming up with some of our fave Shakespeareans at @frigidnewyork for their Little Shakespeare Festival next month and we want to see you there! 

More details to come, but for now, bask in the glory of these talented actors who will make you say, #SHREWYOU! 

Shrew You! is a comedic, no boys allowed, one-act rewrite of Shakespeare‚Äôs most sexist work: The Taming of the Shrew. Ready with an ensemble of four fantastic women, the #HIDiots reimagine and find some joy in the tragedy of Taming, while also telling the Bard to kindly, on behalf of all women, kiss our collective ass.

Your donations will steer the action as the #HIDiots play their way through one of our favorite comedies. Choose the action, choose the accents, choose to celebrate ten years of Hamlet Isn't Dead!

We are THRILLED to announce the launch of our 2023-24 season with our 29th mainstage production: Antony and Cleopatra! John Hughes meets Joan Jett in this infamous tragic romance where passion, pride, and duty are all at odds. Come see our Co-Directors' 80s-inspired epic for two weekends only this October. Stay tuned for our ticket launch within the next week...you aren't going to want to miss this one!

Design by Josh Stauffer (@avoidohio)

Mark your calendars for the fourth and final entry into our Contemporaries of Color series: Matsukaze, The Wind in the Pine, a classic Noh piece of theatre from 14th century Japan.

Join three of Hamlet Isn't Dead's resident acting company members and guest director Saki Kawamura for this incredible story. Get swept away in the emotional journey of sisters Matzukaze and Murasame in this one-of-a-kind digital production.
